caption: I regularly come getting some food here. I like the prompt service and well cooked dishes. Never disappointing.
The spot is awesome and broad, the menu was yummy and the rates were very affordable. fast, productive service and very amiable staff. Will definitely recommend this spot.
Worst ramen I’ve ever had! Never paying this place again. The broth flavor was lackluster, the egg was plain, and the pork was nearly all fat. Extremely disappointed. :(
Fantastic food, nice staff, consistently excellent atmosphere. They charge reasonable rates and the food quality is awesome. Kudos.

This place is my first choice place.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this place. Whenever  I want to go to a proper lunch, this restaurant comes straight to my mind. fresh and all kinds of  food and a large menu.professional staff, and nice atmosphere. Not less important, the price is modest. I recommend this spot with no doubt.

I celebrated my nomination this evening in this fine place. I am glad to say that we had a delightful evening and the venue was clearly one of the reasons for that fruitful evening. The crew  cooperated in a sweet way, the food was great and my guests were very  overjoyed. We shall definitely visit again for more celebrations. thanks very much.
Had a excellent experience here with my kid. The food came quick and the customer service is just awesome. Prices are reasonable.

I adore this place! They prepare marvelous food, they have a rich menu, The chief cook in that restaurant is a professional, I enjoy a lot tasting all their food. The food is always of high qualtity, the attitude towards the clients  is helpful. I  go often to this place and I was never unsatisfied.  I highly recommend it.
Very delicious
Best ramen in Maryland! Flavor is 🔥
I simply enjoy their food. I always get fantastic service here. The place is always clean and the staff members are always friendly. Will come back again.

We love to go out. Yesterday we went to this magnificent place which friends told us about. We had a beautiful evening there with first-rate cooking and  an experienced crew and  a professional  cuisine. We put this venue in our phone list  and we shall surely come back soon. We deeply recommend.
We just had delivered and was really excellent,  even when delivered, which is hard to do.

I frequent this special restaurant from time to time  as I like the good mood that is characterizes this restaurant. The crew is exceptionally cordial and skilfull. The service is extremely quick. Also, the food you get is excellent. I ate there more than once and I was never disappointed. The rate is reasobable. I highly recommend this restaurant to all my friends.

Ordered one of the spicy ramen noodle soups. Soup was extremely spicy. Too spicy to enjoy and I like spicy. The noodles and toppings were great but again, the the spiciness was too overwhelming. I could taste jalapenos for some reason. The server was not friendly or welcoming at all. No hello, no welcome, no how's the food, etc. I asked if they had any non alcoholic drinks. He said "we have soda". I asked if they had smoothies, teas or special drinks. He said "no". After he left I looked at the menu and found some Korean and Japanese drinks. I ordered a Milkis, which I enjoyed. Server should've been more helpful as it was not busy aside from about 3 tables. Have been served by this server previously. Not sure if he is part owner or manager, but always had same non enthusiastic attitude.  3 stars because, aside from overwhelmingly spicy soup and not so courteous server, I think the food is good and I would like to try a non spicy option of the ramen.  That I could see, there is no obvious sign outside that says Saburo Ramen Bar. Saburo is part of Kangnam BBQ and basically the same restaurant. Just have a separate seating area.
Had a good experience in this spot with my son. The food comes out quick and the service is just great. Prices are fair.

It was my 2nd time here and I loved my second choice. The t spicy ramen with pork was amazing. We were exhausted after days work and felt the hot spicy ramen satisfy our taste buds. The music was bit loud for our tiring day. The red and black ramen was my first choice but I highly recommend my second choice. But now it's time. Need more default vegan options on the menu, shaving off 1 star. I would give it back if the ask is satisfied.
Would definitely recommend trying this place. Awesome mood, tasty food, excellent customer service. Keep it up.
Driven past this spot 100 times never would I thought the food would be so good. They put effort into the ramen
One of my preferred spots to eat. very good location, clean, and good customer service. Keep it up!
Great food, helpful staff members, regularly fantastic mood. They charge affordable rates and the food quality is great. 5 stars.

I would like to give it 5 stars because I frequent this place a lot. I’m a big fan of the ramen. But the service just gets worse every time. The waiter is very rude, will not offer refills. & literally said splitting a check was too much work. Needs better service ASAP.
Spice soups

I come to this outstanding restaurant many times since I like the special air that is outline this restaurant. The crew is extremely welcoming and professional. The service is extraordinarily efficient. Most important, the food you eat is exceptionaly good. I visited many times and I was always satisfied. The cost is modest. I highly suggest this restaurant to to all.
Went to try ramen for the first time and was not impressed.
Was just horrible
So delicious!
Fantastic and delicious food, I loved the vibes the spot has, and the cashiers were very nice. I will surely come back again.

This place ain't it. Their tonkotsu ramen was probably some of the worst ramen I've had in the DMV area in a while. I've had mediocre ramen, but this was just terrible. The broth was bland, almost like Top Ramen; the noodles tasted store-bought and a bit mushy; the bamboo shoots were sweet (I have no idea why); no nori in sight, which common for tonkotsu ramen; and the egg was on the hard-boiled side not runny. The service wasn't bad, but it wasn't good either. The portions were ok, nothing extravagant. And they use Party City-quality soup spoons. I think for $12 a bowl, they could spend a little bit on upgrading to regular soup spoons.
Actual heat in the hot dishes and richness cut by the umami of the broth.
Food is always amazing!

This restaurant has two sides, a Ramen side and the barbecue side. I've only been to the ramen side and have ordered both their Ramen soups and their bibimbop, and they were both excellent. The restaurant service needs a little Improvement as they always seem to be understaffed, however the management really goes out of their way to correct mistakes. For example are bibimbop Hot Pot was given to another table by mistake. We were given a dish to munch on for free until our order was done over. This is why I gave them five stars oh, they really make a great effort to ensure that people enjoy their food. Their parking lot is very small, however there is parking available across the street. Well worth the visit for great food.
Very salty miso noodle soup and tough charsui pork. Eggs was cold. They really should be room temperature. Charsui should be soft and tender. Not acceptable for $14 a bowl. It was better a year ago.
Well seasoned food. Quick polite service.

First time there. Food was good and the portions were generous. If there was a weakness it was the attentiveness of the staff to the customers. Not sure if it was intentional or just short in staff. Will have to do more research, especially when the weather cools. See you soon!!!!
Inside of the korean bbq place and same owner. Mediocre ramen and broth. Broth is kinda watery and bland. Saw the chief put his whole hand in the ramen bowl without gloves.
Service pretty slow, often distracted and pay more attention to new customers at the expense of those already there.
Delicious Ramen, not to mention bomb Thai and Mango bubba tea. It's a must and one of the greatest ramen places in the area.

Very disappointed. After reading all the reviews I was expecting a pretty good ramen. Ordered the Tonkotsu White ramen, it was super bland with a weird - detergent like - smell and after taste. Couldn't finish it. ☹️ Also, service was terrible

The food was good but it was the service that wasn't great. I think they were maybe under staffed. There was only 1 guy and we were stuck waiting for our food when its sitting on the counter ready. And had to wait almost 10 min just for some white rice. It was odd bc there was like no one but us
Great food and quick service
Good local ramen joint, will definitely be back to try the other stuff on the menu!
Very good spicy shoyu ramen

"It was really good" - my wife  It was our first time trying the place and we wanted to give it a shot after talking about it for a month. Was not disappointed, the tako-yaki still made my wife craving for more despite hating the taste of fish, and the ramen was just phenomenal overall

In my experience, if I were you, I will stick to the ramen. We had the TONKOTSU SPICY with pork, which was excellent and actually spicy. Also, we got the GALBI HOT STONE BIBIMBAP, which was excessively burned and tasteless.
I love this place! The tonkatsu white is my favorite, and honestly the most flavorful of any I have tried in the surrounding areas.
Best ramen in college Park, and there is some competition now. I love the t black and red, so spicy.   Great place for a ramen lunch.
Loved the flavor of the broth and the noodles and chicken were great too 👍
I come here just about every Sunday. Always a good meal imho.

Nice! The ramen was pretty good. We all enjoyed. So we had T-tokyo with extra egg, my friend had paitan and that was delicious as well. We also had the tako-yaki and Korean steamed dumplings for an appetizers both were also delicious. I like Saburo's tako-yaki better than Bonchon. Also, the soy sauce is house made and delicious.
very cozy environment, nice staff, and the ramen is amazing!

I was surprised to finally find local ramen shop. Not bad I will admit food taste better than oodles of noodles 😋. Long wait tho wasn't mad for the wait just saying the wait was a little longer than I would have liked. Also I get if one person orders a single item but there is no reason 2 or more people should get there food before you......Great atmosphere.could use well better host maybe idk better management. Host lost our order even though they took both orders in same composition notebook.

I come here all the time for Red and black Tonkatsu ramen.  It's one of my favorite.  There's a nice spicy garlic oil seasoning to compliment the creamy smooth pork bone broth. Don't forget to order some octopus takoyaki to munch on while you wait for your Ramen.  If you're thinking of coming here for a bite I definitely suggest you do.

Writing this from SF where I've been trying to find a good ramen spot. This place is, so far, beating out what I've been able to find out here. Delicious broth, great portions and good drink menu. So happy to have it near home. Will be heading there asap when I get back!
Gyoza was great. I can eat 3 orders by myself. Ramen also has great broth.
Good!
Pretty decent ramen with bold flavors. The spicy miso packs some heat.

Very good ramen and gyoza! Have been a few times and hope to be back! The atmosphere is really cool, TVs playing vintage samurai movies or Studio Ghibli films was super cool. Wide variety of beer options as well. Staff was very nice, just go!
Fantastic ramen. Nice staff. DC quality ramen in college park.
Good!! Sake here is good too.
Red and Black ramen was amazing! Definitely recommend!
Food is good here! Spicy😋
The place is not fancy, but I'm there for the delicious food. The Ramen is very tasty, and they also have Korean BBQ in the back.
I HIGHLY enjoyed the ramen. The atmosphere was very relaxed. This is a quick getaway to something different

Very good Ramen some of the best I've had in MD so far. The restaurant has a very nice Japanese vibe which I love. I ordered the Black T with straight noodles and it was very good! One of my favorite broths. If the pork was better it would be perfect. If you like spicy get the spicy Miso, it is very good.  Next time I will try the korean BBQ, I have heard great things

The Saburo Ramen bar is part of a Korean BBQ restaurant.  The ramen was good and there was a range of flavors. I had the chicken and my son had the tonkatsu. The noodles were the best part. Parking is horrible but the food and service is worth it.
If you're considering eating BBQ here, don't. 12/8/18 - 2 people running the floor, questionable meat taste, and no proper service coordination.
One of our favorite spots. Love the T-White Ramen 😋

The food was really good. They have good beers too. Service is fast. It's also affordable. It's hard to find stuff members around when you need them. Also, before drinking water here, make sure that the good doesn't smell like feet. Other than these, the food was great. I would recommend this place if you're craving for ramen.
Delicious Ramen! Needs more wait staff.

Always great food. WARNING do not expect good service 30 mims before they close. We felt rushed out immediatly entering and sitting down. Our server was hovering and brought out the check without being asked. We left before finishing our ramen. Egg was meh. WANING!! I found a hair in my rice and ramen. Very disappointing. Usually a great time. Thanks Andrew.. and hairs
OMG! The spicy tonkotsu was amazing! Almost if not slightly better than toki underground. Broth was on point. And the tonkotsu black was just as good. Highly recommend for two bowls for 22 bucks

Only giving 4 stars as it's the only time I've been here. First impressions are great. I had the "T-spicy" which is just a spicy tonkatsu bowl. Broth was nice and oily, spice was very peppery, and the noodles we good. Overall no real complaints. I'll definitely try and make it back here.
Quietly tucked away within a Korean bbq joint. Delicious food and good prices for the large servings! So happy I found this place. Try the sukiyaki beef and rice, fire asf dog 😻😻😻
This place gave me the runs for 2 days . Never again

First time eating here since the Saburo Ramen Bar opened.  The ramen bar is inside the Korean BBQ restaurant KangNam. The Black-Red Ramen, Curry-Ramen, and the lunch special (they have it Mon-Sat) Bibimbap were all delicious and very reasonably priced.  Highly recommended.
Great ramen.
Very authentic and tasty. Appetizers are great as well.

(Translated by Google) The environment is very good, the service is enthusiastic, the ramen tastes good, the beef snack I ordered, thought it was a side dish, it turned out to be with rice, but the taste is excellent, recommended  (Original) 环境挺好，服务热情，拉面味道不错，点的牛肉小吃，以为是小菜，竟然是带米饭的，不过味道特赞，推荐
Excellent food

If you want to eat wildly excessive quantities of meat, this is the place to go. The AYCE dinner isn't particularly cheap or anything, but you can easily get in more than your money's worth. They also keep giving you more side dishes to go with all the meat (that they cook for you, right at your table!), so… yeah! Good food! Not too expensive! Try it out!

Love the place! I ordered Tonkotsu black and red, which satisfied my love for black garlic oil and spicy food. I love the chashu inside without too much fat. And the half boiled egg, you know it’s delicious. All my friends love their ramen and we decided to check everything on the menu from now on. It’s the best ramen within 20-minute drive from UMD, I think.
Good food

I had a hard time deciding between a 3 and 4 for this place, but I'll give them the benefit of the doubt. The wait staff and ramen chef were really nice. The chef actually directly talked with me and we joked around a bit. Great guy. The ramen is self is more of a 3 out of 5. I've had better at many other places around the district, but overall it wasn't bad, super filling, and had a good price (11 dollars for ramen is on the low end). The place was clean and had a fun atmosphere. Had a good selection of alcohol and drinks. Had a small parking lot in the side that could fill up pretty fast.

Amazing ramen with amazing customer service gives this place five stars! The place is new and well maintained, the bathrooms are nice, parking is ok, the ramen is very good, and the customer service is super friendly. I went with 9 other friends and they were more than happy to accommodate for us and there was no wait time (on a Friday night). It is a little hard to see this restaurant, but it is in an orange building so that helps. Overall I was extremely happy with the food and service here!
Really good ramen especially if you can’t go to DC.

The ramen here is close enough to authentic, it's good comfort food and the quality is good and consistent. The only thing that I would say needs improvement is the soup, which is thin enough for me to notice. Otherwise, the flavors and toppings are what one would expect out of a real ramen place. Would recommend trying it at the very least.  The service quality is questionable though, the waiter seems to be overburdened with tasks and has gotten my group's orders mixed up every time.

Tasty ramen. I got tonkotsu curry kind! All the ingredients were flavorful. The char siu pork slices were a little tough, but filling and big. I wouldn't say it's gourmet, but it's definitely a great option for a quick and different meal.  The ramen bar is inside a Korean BBQ restaurant, so don't be fooled if you don't immediately see ramen in the name.  The inside decor has character-  lots of wood and traditional ramen banners and things like that. A Ghibli movie was playing on a big tv, and there was Vocaloid and other jpop music playing too!  The chef was friendly and happy to be there, which was nice. I'd go back if I'm in the area again!

Just went here for Valentine's Day to check out the new ramen place inside of Kangnam BBQ and what an awesome experience. The chef and his co-worker were both very friendly and funny plus the food was delicious. Best Ramen in the area for sure and we will be going back!
The staff is SUPER friendly! Chefs were so kind and willing to go out of the way to help with orders. Great service :)
The chef is pretty awesome so are the noodles.

I rarely leave reviews but I absolutely had to! This is a great, quaint spot and the ramen is absolutely delicious! Considering authentic ramen is my favorite food, I’ve had plenty and the ramen here is wonderful! I ordered the spicy miso chicken broth with chashu on the side along with the pork gyoza and I was pleasantly surprised and delighted at how wonderful both tasted! My significant other doesn’t even eat pork and when he tried one of the dumplings, he ordered three more servings of them! The sauce that is served with the dumplings is great! Spicy and great flavor. Furthermore, The owner/chef is so kind and really made the dining experience that much nicer. He was so accommodating and personable! With that being said, I am so happy to have found this wonderful restaurant! I will definitely be back!

Amazing ramen with excellent service, based on my personal experience in Japan, this is better than top ramen places in Japan.  Exceptional ramen with friendly staff with quick service. We will be back again.
